<TITLE>LIMITS Project</TITLE>
<H1>L.I.M.I.T.S. PROJECT:</H1>
<H2>Linking Important Medical Information To Students</H2>
<HR>
<A HREF="gopher://141.106.32.47/1MacintoshHD%3aLibrary%3aLIMITS%3a">Go to LIMITS Demo</A> , <A HREF="/LIMITS/LIMITSdetail.html"> Detailed Project Description</A>
<HR>
<H3>Brief Description</H3>

The LIMITS project is an attempt to create a new method of 
providing access to relevant medical literature for students.  
The goal of this project is to overcome physical obstacles by 
providing readily accessible electronic information 24 hours 
a day to any location with Internet access.<P>

The LIMITS project consists of a core database of selected 
references to the medical literature (Medline abstracts) with 
indexing links to common medical problems.  In addition, 
annotations or reviewers comments can be appended to the 
abstracts to further clarify the usefulness or relevance of 
a particular article.<P>

Initially this pilot project will consist of indexing 500 core articles on 80-100 common clinical problems with selected annotations.  We plan to implement a WWW forms based system for submitting additional articles for inclusion on this system.<HR>
<H4>Please send your comments or requests for additional information to:<BR>
Gary P. Barnas, M.D. <A HREF ="mailto:barnas@post.its.mcw.edu">barnas@post.its.mcw.edu</A></H4>
<HR>
<ADDRESS>Last Update: 1/6/95</ADDRESS> 
<A HREF="http://www.intmed.mcw.edu/">Return to MCW-GIM Home Page</A> ,  
