    <tr>
        <td><font size="4"><strong>&quot;I have always admired
        professionals like Richard Alexander, who continuously
        and voluntarily devote their knowledge and their energy
        to improving their field in a way that will benefit a
        larger public . . . he has dedicated his law firm to
        defending consumer rights and prosecuting class actions
        for consumers and small businesses across the United
        States.&quot;</strong></font><blockquote>
            <blockquote>
                <p><font size="3">Tom Hayes, Director of
                Corporate Affairs for Applied Materials, Inc.,
                founding chairman of Joint Venture: Silicon
                Valley and author of <strong>You Can Make A
                Difference In Silicon Valley</strong>. </font></p>
            </blockquote>
        </blockquote>
        <p><font size="5">&quot;</font><font size="4">While it is
        often said that the 'past is prologue,' a testimonial,
        endorsement or result in a particular case does not
        constitute a promise, prediction or guarantee regarding
        the outcome of any other case. For those whom we
        represent The Alexander Law Firm commits its best
        efforts. Those efforts over the years are reported here.
        Each case was dependent on a multiplicity of factors and
        unique facts. Because of many different factors, results
        always will differ from case to case. For that reason the
        results that we obtained in these cases are no guarantee
        that we can again achieve the same results in any future
        case. In fact to understand what we achieved in these
        cases we have provided a substantial amount of
        information, including references to news articles and
        court files, so anyone can evaluate and make their own
        determination of the result and our record. There is only
        common factor in all the cases reported here: the
        plaintiff was represented by Richard Alexander or The
        Alexander Law Firm.&quot;</font> </p>
        <p align="right"><font size="4"><em>-- Richard Alexander</em></font>
        </p>
        <p><font size="4">The Alexander Law Firm focuses on
        consumer and commercial class actions arising from
        negligence, toxic chemicals, defective products, mass
        accidents, environmental and fraud cases. Our firm was
        founded by Richard Alexander one of the first lawyers in
        the United States certified as a Diplomate of the
        National Board of Trial Advocacy. A graduate of the
        University of Chicago Law School, he is Past President of
        the Santa Clara County Bar Association, and is a former
        Governor of the State Bar of California. The Alexander
        Law Firm practices a &quot;client-centered&quot; approach
        based on </font><a href="talfstat.html"><font size="4">shared
        decision making</font></a><font size="4"> and expects
        clients to fully participate in the decisions that affect
        their case. </font></p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
</center></div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
