poison(s) environmental mass accident negligence aircrash, lives located resides practices california northern san jose nationally united states --><h2><a href="index.html#menu">The Alexander Law Firm:</a> ABOUT OUR FIRM</h2>
<p>On this page:</p>
<p><a href="#philosophy"><img src="t-dn.gif" alt="**" align=middle width=20 height=35></a> <a href="#philosophy">Our Philosophy</a> || <a href="#team"><img src="t-dn.gif" alt="**" align=middle width=20 height=35></a> <a href="#team">Our Team Members</a></p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="philosophy">OUR PHILOSOPHY</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#intro">Introduction</a> </li>
<li><a href="#partner">Your Lawyer - Your Partner</a> </li>
<li><a href="#people">The People Who Make a Difference</a> </li>
<li><a href="#resources">Resources</a> </li>
<li><a href="#readiness">Readiness</a> </li>
<li><a href="#results">Results</a> </li>
</ul>
<p><a name="intro"><strong>COMMITTED TO MAKING A DIFFERENCE FOR YOU AND THE COMMUNITY</strong></a></p>
<p>The Alexander Law Firm is committed to making a difference for our clients and to contributing to the improvement of life in 
our community and our country.</p>
<p>We represent consumers and owners of small businesses across the United States. Our expertise is in negligence, <a href="txt/intro.html#toxic">toxic 
chemical</a>, <a href="txt/intro.html#product">defective product</a>, mass accident, <a href="txt/intro.html#toxic">environmental</a>, and consumer fraud cases for individuals and in class actions, a 
powerful legal procedure for holding accountable wrongdoers who have injured groups of individuals.</p>
<p><a name="partner"><strong>YOUR LAWYER - YOUR PARTNER</strong></a></p>
<p>We only agree to represent clients for whom we can make a difference and with whom we share a common commitment to a 
common cause. It is the reason why we are known for our enthusiasm and driving effort to obtain a just result.</p>
<p>When we agree to become your attorneys we work on a contingency fee basis. We do not expect to be paid unless we are 
successful and under a written agreement we promise to bear the cost of preparing a case for trial. As long as our clients 
follow our advice, if there is no recovery, there are no charges: no fees and no costs.</p>
<p>If we are successful in a class action case, we petition the court for our fees to be paid as a percentage of a common fund or 
to order the wrongdoer to pay our fees. We view our relationship as a special responsibility and a partnership with our clients. 
As in any partnership we require that our clients work closely <strong>with us</strong> to assure shared and informed decision-making.</p>
<p><a name="people"><strong>THE PEOPLE WHO MAKE A DIFFERENCE</strong></a></p>
<p>Decades of experience in challenging litigation bring to The Alexander Law Firm an enviable infrastructure of staff, 
researchers, and experts who play a crucial role in preparing winning cases.</p>
<p>The firm's tight focus on difficult, complex cases for individuals and small businesses in negligence, <a href="txt/intro.html#toxic">toxic chemical</a>, <a href="txt/intro.html#product">defective 
product</a>, mass accident, <a href="txt/intro.html#toxic">environmental</a> and fraud cases provides a professional environment for these individuals to excel in 
developing leading-edge evidentiary techniques. This makes for second-to-none &quot;tactical support&quot;--an invaluable asset for any 
client.</p>
<p>All these things allow you to be confident that the firm will represent you in the most professional, exhaustive, and resolute 
manner.</p>
<p><a name="resources"><strong>RESOURCES</strong></a></p>
<p>Giving a client a 110% effort means not skimping on evidentiary resources. An example? When a BMW needed to be 
purchased and crashed to prove a point--we didn't hesitate. In fact, <i>we crashed two</i>. Whether it's a <a href="txt/compute.html">computer simulation</a> of a 
toxic cloud, a microscopic inspection of airborne asbestos, high speed photography of a gas tank failure, or complex 
programming to prove damages for homeowners living on defective foundations, we throw the full weight of audio, visual and 
sensory elements at making a case. Mastering these and other sophisticated technologies has become an essential tool in our 
practice.</p>
<p>Doing these kinds of things takes money--quite often, lots of it. We bear all costs in preparing a case. It's another investment 
we take very seriously. When faced with serious damages and institutions looking to protect their financial interests, our clients 
regard this financial capacity quite literally as the opened door to justice.</p>
<p><a name="readiness"><strong>READINESS</strong></a></p>
<p>Because we limit our practice we are able to focus our resources and skills to act quickly, forcefully and effectively. When a 
client is accepted, momentum is immediate. Years of representing clients with challenging cases has taught us the value of 
keeping cases moving. We know and understand that our opponents are afraid of the courtroom, where the public will learn 
the truth, so we push to bring our client's cases to trial, while striving to create imaginative solutions that are in our client's 
interest. Nothing brings about a defendant's willingness to act reasonably more quickly than 12 jurors ready to hear all the 
evidence we have mustered.</p>
<p><a name="results"><strong>RESULTS</strong></a></p>
<p>We believe the difference between getting an expedient settlement and a just award often comes down to an attorney's innate 
determination, spirit and commitment. Settling too low can stem from lack of preparation or a lack of will. Getting justice 
demands both solid case preparation and the will to insist on a fair result. Many claim that they can deliver. We prefer facts 
and on these pages we open our record for your inspection.</p>
<p>We have a strong record of success confronting wrongdoers who have taken from our clients their property and have injured 
their well-being. Not the type of tyrant and oppressor fought two centuries ago on village greens with muskets, but modern 
day Redcoats who can be equally arrogant in their efforts to avoid responsibility for the damage they have caused. We meet 
them in the courtroom and we fight with facts before juries of citizens that we trust to follow the law and to separate fact from 
fiction. Some say that our success is due to a &quot;tough&quot; attitude . We call it having a passion for justice and fairness. It's why we 
have chosen 1776 to identify our practice. </p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="team">MEMBERS OF THE FIRM</a></h3>
<p><strong>RICHARD ALEXANDER </strong>is certified as a Civil Trial Attorney by the National Board of Trial Advocacy and recognized as 
a Trial Lawyer by the Consumer Attorneys of California. After graduating from Ohio Wesleyan University, where he was the 
Owens-Illinois Scholar and elected to Pi Sigma Alpha [national political science honorary], he was awarded a National Honor 
Scholarship by the University of Chicago Law School, where he graduated in 1969. A Past President of the Santa Clara 
County Bar, former Governor of The State Bar of California and Vice President of CAOC, he is a regular lecturer at legal 
seminars and a founding member of the National Association of Consumer Advocates. The Alexander Law Firm has earned 
Martindale-Hubbell's highest rating and is recognized in the List of Preeminent Law Firms in the United States. </p>
<p><a href="http://seamless.com/malexander/resume_malexander.html"><strong>MICHAEL ALEXANDER</strong></a>, a graduate of the University of Cincinnati School of Law, was admitted to practice in Ohio in 
1976 and anchors the Cincinnati office. A specialist in labor and employment law, collective bargaining, EEOC, age 
discrimination, and harassment matters, he is a member of the Consumer Attorneys of California, Cincinnati Bar Association, 
the Ohio State Bar Association and the National Association of Consumer Advocates. </p>
<p><strong>JONATHAN PENDLETON</strong> earned his B.A. in 1989 from Princeton University in Politics and is a 1992 graduate of the 
University of Michigan Law School. Jon previously was the International Criminal Court Project Coordinator for the 
International Commission of Jurists in Geneva, Switzerland. He is a member of the Santa Clara County Bar and is an original 
member of the National Association of Consumer Advocates. </p>
<p><strong>MICHAEL MCSHANE</strong> graduated from the University of California at Santa Barbara before earning his law degree from 
the University of Oregon in 1986. Mike has ten years experience as a lead attorney in complex class action litigation 
representing plaintiffs. His representative class action experience includes the Southern Pacific Spill at Dunsmuir, General 
Chemical Richmond California Sulfuric Acid Explosion and Neptune burial fraud litigation. He is a member of Consumer 
Attorneys of California, the National Association of Consumer Advocates and the Association of Trial Lawyers of America. </p>
<p><strong>AMANDA HAWES</strong> is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Wellesley College and was awarded a Juris Doctorate by the Harvard 
Law School in 1968. A pioneer in toxic chemical litigation and a storehouse of information on the medical effects of toxic 
chemicals, Mandy has taught environmental justice and toxic torts at Golden Gate University School of Law, Santa Clara Law 
School and the University of California's Hastings College of Law where she was a faculty member from 1975 to 1988. She 
has 20 years experience representing people exposed to toxic chemicals.that have caused cancer, leukemia, autoimmune 
disorders and other diseases. In the Fairchild water contamination cases in Santa Clara County she was the primary 
investigator responsible for assessing the strengths and weaknesses of 500 injury claims due to solvent-contaminated drinking 
water. Mandy is the Founder and former executive director of Santa Clara County Occupational Safety and Health. </p>
<p><strong>ANN SAPONARA</strong> earned her B.A. in 1989 from the University of California, Los Angeles and was awarded a Juris 
Doctorate in 1994 from Cornell Law School. Ann is a recipient of the 1996 California State Bar Wiley W. Manuel Award for 
Pro Bono Service for her volunteer work with the Bar Association of San Francisco.. She is an original member of the 
National Association of Consumer Advocates, Consumer Attorneys of California and the American Trial Lawyers 
Association. </p>
<p><strong>TYLER A. SHAW</strong>, a presidential scholar, graduated magna cum laude from Weber State University in 1988 with a B.A. in 
Oral Communications. Designated as a William F. Leary scholar, Tyler was awarded a Juris Doctorate in 1992 from the 
University of Utah after clerking for the Utah Court of Appeals. A member of Consumer Attorneys of California and San 
Francisco Trial Lawyers Association, Tyler has represented plaintiffs in personal injury and complex litigation since 1993.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Of Counsel:</em> </p>
<p><strong>WILLIAM MICHAEL AUDET</strong> earned a B.A. from the University of California, Davis, in 1981, a Juris Doctor from 
Golden Gate University School of Law in 1984, where he was the Editor of the Golden Gate University Law Review, and 
completed his formal legal education with a Masters of Law from the University of Wisconsin School of Law in 1987. He 
clerked for The Honorable Alfonso J. Zirpoli, United States District Judge for the Northern District of California and The 
Honorable Fern M. Smith, United States District Judge for the Northern District of California; he served as a clerk to the 
court for the U. S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and held a Judicial Internship with Mr. Justice Allen E. Broussard, 
California Supreme Court. A former member of the faculty of the University of Wisconsin School of Law, he is a co-author of 
Handling Federal Discovery [James Publishing Company, 1995] and has in-depth experience specializing in complex litigation 
involving securities, mass torts, product liability, antitrust and consumer class actions. </p>
