<hr>

<p><a href="fight.html"><font size="3"><img src="fight.gif"
alt=" " align="left" hspace="10" width="116" height="66"></font></a><font
size="5">F</font><font size="3">iling a consumer complaint with a
local county consumer agency or the Better Business Bureau, and
in some cases a Small Claims Court lawsuit, can be the best way
to put a stop to consumer abuse by a local wrongdoer. In other
cases, in which consumers are abused by major corporations, only
the power of a consumer class action can correct misdeeds. </font></p>

<p><font size="5">I</font><font size="3">f you already have read </font><a
href="complain.html"><font size="3">How To Resolve Your Consumer
Complaint: Self-Help or Class Action</font></a><font size="3">,
open </font><a href="fight.html"><font size="3">this section</font></a><font
size="3"> and answer a </font><a href="fight.html"><font size="3">short
questionnaire</font></a><font size="3"> to determine if your
consumer fraud could be a class action. There is no charge and
you are not obligated to take any action until you decide to do
so.</font><font size="1">[960318]</font><font size="3"> <br
clear="all">
</font></p>

