<h2><a href="index.html">The Consumer Law Page</a> &#153; : Consumers Fight Back!:</h2>
<hr>
<p><font size=5>F</font>iling a consumer complaint with a local county consumer agency or the Better Business Bureau, and in some cases a Small Claims 
Court lawsuit, can be the best way to put a stop to consumer abuse by a local wrongdoer. In other cases, in which consumers are 
abused by major corporations, only the power of a consumer class action can correct misdeeds. </p>
<p><font size=5>I</font>f you already have read <a href="article/complain.shtml">How To Resolve Your Consumer Complaint: Self-Help or Class Action</a> please answer this short 
questionnaire to help us determine if your consumer fraud could be a class action. There is no charge and you are not obligated to 
take any action until you decide to do so. </p>
<p><font size=5>T</font>he Alexander Law Firm represents individuals, consumers and small businesses from across the U.S. who have suffered damage. 
Every day we are asked to participate in many cases. While we are approached on far more cases than we can accept, we welcome 
your inquiries and if we can help we will. </p>
<p><font size=5>O</font>ur expertise is in negligence, toxic chemical, defective product, environmental, mass accident and fraud cases. As you know from 
the information provided on <a href="http://seamless.com/alexanderlaw">our home page</a> we do not prosecute frivolous cases and offer a substantial range of experience which is 
far beyond that of the traditional plaintiffs' law firm. Our philosophy and our record is set forth in detail on this website and we 
encourage prospective clients to study our record and compare it with others when needing a lawyer. It is difficult finding the &quot;right&quot; 
lawyer for a particular case, but it is an ultimately important decision. If we are not the &quot;right&quot; lawyer for you, we may know the &quot;right&quot; 
lawyer near you who can help you.</p>
<p><font size=5>O</font>ur primary work is representing plaintiffs in <a href="article/complain.shtml#class">class action lawsuits</a> against national and multi-national companies in both federal and 
state courts. A class action is an extremely powerful tool to hold a wrongdoer accountable in circumstances where an individual case 
would be inefficient or uneconomical. We carefully investigate all prospective cases before filing suit. We do not accept frivolous 
lawsuits, because unless we are successful, we are not paid. After the successful conclusion of a class action, we petition the court to 
order the wrongdoer to pay our attorneys fees on behalf of the class and to pay the cost of prosecuting the case. In cases in which a 
common fund has been created to benefit class members, we petition the court to allocate a percentage of the recovery as attorneys 
fees, much the same as in our individual cases.</p>
<p><font size=5>W</font>e accept cases for individuals on a contingency basis. We agree to pay all trial preparation costs necessary to prosecute a case 
and are only paid for our services if, and when, we are successful. We do not send bills or ask for retainers. As long as our clients 
follow our advice, if there is no recovery in either a class action or in an individual case, there is no charge for attorneys fee and the 
costs of prosecuting a case are our responsibility, not yours.</p>
<p><font size=5>T</font>o determine whether or not you have a case that we can accept, we need to know about you, the damages you suffered, the 
persons that caused the damage and what you hope to achieve by working with a qualified lawyer on your problem.</p>
<p><font size=5>T</font>he information you provide in this online questionnaire will be kept confidential and will be sent directly to the electronic mail center 
of The Alexander Law Firm. After we receive your inquiry, we will contact you to discuss how we can help you.</p>
<p><font size=5>R</font>emember, the Internet is not confidential. We do not believe that the large volume of individual email on the net is monitored, but if 
you prefer unquestioned confidentiality you can address a letter to The Alexander Law Firm, P. O. Box 1330, San Jose, CA 
95109-1330 or fax to 408.287.1776 providing the information requested below.</p>
<form action="http://seamless.com/cgi-bin/tsw-talf.pl" method="POST">
<input type=hidden name="reline" value="CLP">
<hr>
<h4>Tell Us Who You Are and How We Can Contact You. </h4>
