<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- looking find locate seeking search lawyer attorney litigation  law firm alexander richard , specializes handles does practices handles
consumer law tort class action(s) product liability defective products  toxic chemical(s)  fraud bodily injury personal injury pollution 
poison(s) environmental mass accident negligence aircrash, lives located resides practices california northern san jose nationally united states --><h2><a name="title">GMC ABS Brake Investigation</a></h2>
<h4>By Richard Alexander </h4>
<hr>
<p><font size=5>R</font>e: 1992 - 1995 GMC AND CHEVROLET SUBURBANS</p>
<p><font size=5>D</font>o you have any problems with your brakes? This includes: </p>
<ul>
<li>Poor brake pedal feel, or unusual brake pedal travel </li>
<li>Excessive front brake pad wear (less than 30,000 miles) </li>
<li>Unexplained bad stopping </li>
<li>Sliding through intersections </li>
<li>Excessive front tire wear </li>
<li>Slow stopping or the feeling that you won't stop in time. </li>
</ul>
<p><font size=5>I</font>f you have any of these problems or others with your brakes, you may have the same problem that others have with the 
Kelsey Hayes anti-lock brake system (ABS). </p>
<p><font size=5>A</font>nother problem is that you may not be aware of all the limitations of the ABS. These limitations also include: </p>
<ul>
<li>ABS can increase stopping distance </li>
<li>ABS can increase stopping distances over non-ABS in certain snow and gravel road situations </li>
<li>The ABS stops operating at 4 mph when stopping </li>
<li>The ABS does not start operating until 8 mph </li>
<li>This system is one of the slowest if not the slowest system available </li>
<li>This system is allegedly not comparable to other GM systems </li>
</ul>
<p><font size=5>T</font>he National Highway Transportation Safety Administration (NHTSA) is also reportedly investigating complaints of poor 
braking in GMC/Chevrolet Suburbans. </p>
<p><font size=5>A</font>s part of our investigation we welcome hearing from you. Would you please complete the following questionnaire? The 
information provided will be kept confidential. </p>
<p><font size=5>I</font>f you know someone with a GMC/Chevrolet Suburbans, please email them and recommend they visit 
http://www.seamless.com/alexanderlaw/txt/absgmc.html -- or printout this questionnaire, and ask the owner to mail it to: </p>
<p><strong>GMC/Chevrolet Suburban ABS Brakes Investigation</strong><br>
The Alexander Law Firm<br>
P.O. Box 1330<br>
San Jose, CA 95109-1330<br>
</p>
<p><font size=5>T</font>hank you for participating with other consumers in this investigation. </p>
