<h2>Tom Nolan: Criminal Defense Lawyer of Choice:</h2>
<h3>The &quot;Right Lawyer&quot; When You Are Charged With a Crime in California or the Western 
Unites States </h3>
<h3>By Richard Alexander, Esq.</h3>
<p><hr><p><font size=-1>
San Jose, California attorney Richard Alexander, a National Honor Scholar at The Law School, University of Chicago, was certified as a civil trial advocate by the National Board of Trial Advocacy in 1980, has been specially recognized as a Trial Lawyer by the California Trial Lawyers Association, is a former member of the Board of Governors of The State Bar of California, currently serves as Vice President of Consumer Attorneys of California and is a founding member of the National Association of Consumer Advocates. He is the founder of <a href="http://www.alexanderlaw.com">The Alexander Law Firm</a> [http://www.alexanderlaw.com], a medium size law firm specializing in individual and class action litigation arising from negligence, toxic chemical, defective product, mass accident, environmental and fraud cases on behalf of consumers and small businesses. The firm holds Martindale-Hubbell's highest rating and is recognized in the List of Preeminent Law Firms in the United States. The firm sponsors <a href=http://consumerlawpage.com>The Consumer Law Page</a> [http://consumerlawpage.com] on the World Wide Web. Copyright Richard Alexander 1996.</font></p>
<hr>

</p>
<p>&quot;If Tom tells you he's going to prove something . . . you can pretty well figure its in the bank. I guess there are some attorneys 
who would welcome the challenge of trying a case against him. But for others it's, Oh no!'&quot; -Jack Marshall, Chief Trial 
Deputy, Santa Clara County D.A.'s Office &quot;Ingenious tactics . . . .&quot;L.A. Times&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;The best money [can] buy&quot; -Randall Sullivan, author, The Price of Experience.</p>
<p>&quot;. . . larger than life reputation as the San Francisco Peninsula's premier criminal defense lawyer.&quot; -San Jose Mercury News</p>
<p>&quot;He is first of all a big hearted, passionate person . . . in court, that personal attribute is amplified and the jury and judge are 
really sold on the idea that he believes what he is saying and the rightness of his client's cause.&quot; -Santa Clara County Superior 
Court Judge Conrad Rushing</p>
<p>Thomas J. Nolan, a nationally recognized criminal defense lawyer, brings nearly thirty years of trial and appellate experience to 
bear for his clients. Known for his ability to obtain success under the most adverse conditions (he once took over a complex 
trade secrets case on the first day of trial and won), Tom approaches each case with the tactical skills of Ghengis Khan, a 
great understanding of human nature, both judges and juries, with an eye towards total victory. </p>
<p>Located in the Silicon Valley, Tom Nolan and his premiere criminal defense firm, Nolan and Armstrong, have substantially 
shaped the practice of high-tech criminal defense in California. From obtaining a dismissal in one of the first major software 
trade secret case, People v. Magnusson, to obtaining acquittal after a four and one half month jury trial in the Intel/ULSI case, 
Tom's successful defense of numerous Silicon Valley notables facing complex business crime prosecutions is legendary. </p>
<p>Author Randall Sullivan captured Nolan's trial presence in the renowned Billionaire Boys Club case, describing Nolan's 
closing argument as moving, &quot;several members of the [jury] panel to tears.&quot; Sullivan continued, &quot;[w]hat worked best for Nolan 
was his decision to place a chair on the courtroom floor only a few feet away from the jury box so that he might sit at 
eye-level with those who would judge his client.&quot; The prosecutor in that case consistently summarized Tom's approach with 
one word: &quot;formidable.&quot;</p>
<p>Recognized around the country by fellow criminal defense lawyers and a former president of California Attorneys for Criminal 
Justice, Tom Nolan maintains a thriving, aggressive practice in both state and federal court. He is certified as a Criminal Law 
Specialist by the State Bar of California, he has served as a member of the Criminal Law Advisory Committee of the State 
Bar; and he was recently inducted into the American College of Trial Lawyers. </p>
<p>Tom has been recognized by the Best Lawyers in America as one of the top criminal defense lawyers in the country. In 
addition, he is a lawyer representative to the Ninth Circuit and a member of the ABA Liaison committee for the Criminal 
Justice Section, having practiced criminal law exclusively since receiving his J.D. from the University of California at Davis in 
1970. </p>
<p>Tom is also a consulting professor at Stanford Law School, teaching classes on White Collar Crime, and Advance Criminal 
Procedure, among others. In addition he lectures throughout the country on criminal defense practice, trial practice and trial 
ethics. He has also been an expert witness on the responsibility of criminal trial lawyers as well as effective assistance of 
counsel. In this capacity he testified as an expert concerning the reasonableness of fees in the Delorean matter. </p>
<p>Tom has developed a law practice that is devoted exclusively to the defense of the citizen accused. Working with partners 
Mike Armstrong and Dan Barton, and associate Rebecca Laibson, the firm comprises a full-service criminal defense firm, 
handling all levels of criminal cases, from the most technically complex, white collar cases to forensically complicated 
homicides to misdemeanor and drunk driving offenses. </p>
<p>Tom has been extremely successful in sheltering clients from adverse publicity and public exposure. The firm also provides top 
quality, discreet representation to low profile clients. The attorneys of the firm assist individuals who face police questioning as 
part of a criminal investigation, who may be called as witnesses, who are being prosecuted in criminal courts, or who need 
representation on appeal. Nolan &amp; Armstrong's practice includes all facets of criminal defense ranging from assistance with 
minor contacts with law enforcement to representation at jury trial. The lawyers of the firm, and with good cause, pride 
themselves on establishing close relationships with their clients in order to best understand and solve their problems. </p>
<p>One interesting aspect of Tom's practice is that he does not advertise. The firm relies upon previous clientele and referrals 
from the legal community for its continued ability to assist people. The firm has received the highest rating (AV) from the 
Martindale-Hubbell Legal Directory and is listed in the Martindale-Hubbell Bar Register of Preeminent Lawyers. </p>
<p>When it comes to hiring the &quot;right lawyer&quot; for a criminal defense in the Western United States, Tom Nolan is our choice. </p>
