        width="116" height="66"></font> </h2>
        <h2 align="center"><a href="../index.html"><font size="4"><tt>The
        Consumer Law Page</tt></font></a><font size="4"><tt> </tt></font><font
        size="2" face="Courier New"><sup><sup><sup><sup><sup><strong>TM</strong></sup></sup></sup></sup></sup></font>
        </h2>
        <div align="center"><center><table border="0"
        width="100%">
            <tr>
                <td align="center" width="50%"><p align="center"><font
                size="5">K</font><font size="4">udos for The
                Alexander Law Firm</font> </p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3"><em><strong>Yahoo
                    Unplugged</strong></em></font></p>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3">David Filo and
                    Jerry Yang, co-founders of <strong>Yahoo</strong>,
                    in their 500 page guide to the Net, <em>Yahoo
                    Unplugged</em>, feature only two law firms. </font></p>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3">&quot;</font><a
                    href="http://consumerlawpage.com"><font
                    size="3">The Consumer Law Page</font></a><font
                    size="3"> presented by the </font><a
                    href="http://seamless.com/alexanderlaw/"><font
                    size="3">Alexander Law Firm</font></a><font
                    size="3">, specialists in consumer product
                    liability, links to Netwide consumer interest
                    resources, contains more than 100 consumer
                    information brochures and articles on such
                    topics of interest as product liability and
                    toxic torts. <strong>An excellent and
                    generous commercial site</strong>.&quot; </font></p>
                </blockquote>
                <blockquote>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3"><em>T</em><em><strong>he
                    Web Magazine</strong></em><strong>,
                    December/January 1997, p. 79</strong></font></p>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3">&quot;Here's a
                    rarity: a site promoting a law firm that's
                    still worth the trek. You get excellent
                    articles covering all kinds of grist for
                    lawsuits (from faulty brakes to Gulf War
                    Syndrome), consumer education brochures, and
                    hundreds of links. The </font><a
                    href="nccc/cb-intro.html"><font size="3">National
                    Consumer Complaint Center</font></a><font
                    size="3"> provides an electronic form you can
                    fill out to detail the ways you've been
                    bilked; and the firm will forward your
                    complaint to 'agencies interested in
                    investigating and taking action for
                    consumers.'&quot;</font></p>
                    <p align="left"><font size="3">Ratings:
                    Content - 5, Links - 4, Overall - 4</font></p>
