<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!--looking find locate seeking search lawyer attorney litigation  law firm alexander richard , specializes handles does practices handles
consumer law tort class action(s) product liability defective products  toxic chemical(s)  fraud bodily injury personal injury pollution 
poison(s) environmental mass accident negligence aircrash, lives located resides practices california northern san jose nationally united states --><h2><a href="index.html#menu">The Alexander Law Firm:</a> How To Become an Alexander Law Firm Client</h2>
<hr>
<p>The Alexander Law Firm represents individuals, consumers and small businesses from across the U.S. who have suffered damage. Every day we are asked to 
participate in many cases. While we are approached on far more cases than we can accept, we welcome your inquiries and if we can help we will. </p>
<p>Our expertise is in negligence, toxic chemical, defective product, environmental, mass accident and fraud cases. As you know from the information provided on <a href="talf.html">our 
home page</a> we do not prosecute frivolous cases and offer a substantial range of experience which is far beyond that of the traditional plaintiffs' law firm. Our 
philosophy and our record is set forth in detail on this website and we encourage prospective clients to study our record and compare it with others when needing a 
lawyer. It is difficult finding the &quot;right&quot; lawyer for a particular case, but it is an ultimately important decision. If we are not the &quot;right&quot; lawyer for you, we may know 
the &quot;right&quot; lawyer near you who can help you. To help you find the right lawyer we have written an article explaining an approach that will make sure you are getting 
advice from a well qualified and experienced professional: <a href="txt/article/howhire.shtml">How to Hire the &quot;Right Lawyer&quot;: Consumers' Rights on the Legal Marketplace. </a></p>
<p>The Alexander Law Firm represents plaintiffs in cases of serious injuries, wrongful death and in <a href="txt/complain.html#class">class action lawsuits</a> against national and multi-national companies in 
both federal and state courts. A class action is an extremely powerful tool to hold a wrongdoer accountable in circumstances where an individual case would be 
inefficient or uneconomical. To review our experience in a wide range of cases, check our <a href="cases.html">record</a>.</p>
<p>We carefully investigate all prospective cases before filing suit. We do not accept frivolous lawsuits, because unless we are successful, we are not paid. After the 
successful conclusion of a class action, we petition the court to order the wrongdoer to pay our attorneys fees on behalf of the class and to pay the cost of 
prosecuting the case. In cases in which a common fund has been created to benefit class members, we petition the court to allocate a percentage of the recovery as 
attorneys fees, much the same as in our individual cases.</p>
<p>We accept cases for individuals on a contingency basis. We agree to pay all trial preparation costs necessary to prosecute a case and are only paid for our services 
if, and when, we are successful. We do not send bills or ask for retainers. As long as our clients follow our advice, if there is no recovery in either a class action or 
in an individual case, there is no charge for attorneys fee and the costs of prosecuting a case are our responsibility, not yours.</p>
<p>To determine whether or not you have a case that we can accept, we need to know about you, the damages you suffered, the persons that caused the damage and 
what you hope to achieve by working with a qualified lawyer on your problem.</p>
<p>The information you provide in this online questionnaire will be kept confidential and will be sent directly to the electronic mail center of The Alexander Law Firm. 
After we receive your inquiry, we will contact you to discuss how we can help you.</p>
<p>Remember, the Internet is not confidential. We do not believe that the large volume of individual email on the net is monitored, but if you prefer unquestioned 
confidentiality you can address a letter to The Alexander Law Firm, P. O. Box 1330, San Jose, CA 95109-1330 or fax to 408.287.1776 providing the information 
requested below.</p>
<form action="http://seamless.com/cgi-bin/tsw-talf.pl" method="POST">
<input type=hidden name="reline" value="ALF">
<hr>
<h4>Tell Us Who You Are and How We Can Contact You. </h4>
<p><input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="first-name"> First Name<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="last-name"> Last Name<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="number-street"> Number, Street &amp; Apt.<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="city"> City<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="state"> State<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=20 name="zip"> Zip <br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="email"> E-mail (Required)<br>
<input type=text size=15 maxlength=20 name="day-phone"> Day Phone<br>
<input type=text size=15 maxlength=20 name="night-phone"> Night Phone<br>
<input type=text size=15 maxlength=50 name="fax" ALIGN="left"> Fax<br>
</p>
<hr>
<h4>Provide Us A Brief Personal Background of the Person Needing Assistance.</h4>
<p>Many times we are contacted by someone other than the person in need of help, such as a parent on behalf of a child, or wife on behalf of a husband. Please 
provide the following information on behalf of person who needs assistance.</p>
<p>The following information is for myself: <input type=radio name="myself" value="myself">Yes <input type=radio name="myself" value="other person">No</p>
<p>If &quot;no,&quot; my relationship to the following person is: <input type=text size=40 maxlength=50 name="relation"></p>
<p><input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="rel-first-name"> First Name<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="rel-last-name"> Last Name<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="age"> Age<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="occupation"> Occupation<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="how-long"> For how long<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="employer"> Current or last employer<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="city-state"> City and state where last employed<br>
<input type=text size=20 maxlength=50 name="highest-grade"> Highest grade completed<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="schools"> Schools/College attended<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="degrees"> Degrees<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="year-granted"> Year degree granted<br>
<input type=text size=30 maxlength=50 name="training"> Special training or experience in<br>
</p>
<hr>
<h4>Why Do You Need Help?</h4>
<p>Please provide us with a very brief summary, in 15 words or less, describing in general the subject matter of your request. <strong>You can provide more detailed 
information later</strong>, but <em>for now please confine yourself to providing us with a brief overview</em>. Here are some examples of what your summary should say.</p>
<p><strong>Consumer Fraud Examples</strong>: Insurance company discriminates against people with X condition or disabilaity; ABC Company is defrauding consumers who buy 
its lightbulbs; my contact lens company sells three different lenses which can be worn for different periods at different prices, but they are all the same product.</p>
<p><strong>Small Business Examples</strong>: I have a franchise with XYZ Corporation and other franchisees are getting preferential treatment; RST Company took a down 
payment for a franchise and never returned my money.</p>
<p><strong>Toxic Chemical Examples</strong>: I worked with strong chemicals for years and was just diagnosed with leukemia; the EPA just told us that our home is built on a toxic 
waste disposal site.</p>
<p><strong>Defective Product Examples</strong>: My minivan has been recalled three times and still overheats; the gas tank exploded and caused . . . . .</p>
<p><strong>Mass Accident Examples</strong>: a tank car of sulfuric acid exploded and the fumes injured my lungs; an electrical transformer exploded and caused . . . . . </p>
<p>Please type a very brief summary, in 15 words or less, describing in general the subject matter of your request in the box below.</p>
<ul>
<li><input type=text size=40 maxlength=90 name="summary"></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>State the date you were injured or when you first learned that you had been damaged?</h4>
<ul>
<li><input type=text size=20 maxlength=256 name="DDMMYY" ROWS="1" COLS="10" ALIGN="left"> DDMMYY</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>How did you find out?</h4>
<p>For example: when it happened; my doctor diagnosed my child with X; the bank told me they could not make the loan because my land was poisoned.Please type 
in the box below how you found out:</p>
<ul>
<li><input type=text size=40 maxlength=256 name="find-out" ROWS="1" COLS="20" ALIGN="left"></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>Where did it happen?</h4>
<p>Please type in the City and State where it happened in the box below:</p>
<ul>
<li><input type=text size=40 maxlength=256 name="where-happened" ROWS="1" COLS="40" ALIGN="left"></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>Who do you suspect or believe caused the harm?</h4>
<p>Please type in the names of all the wrongdoers involved below:</p>
<ul>
<li><textarea name="wrongdoers" rows=3 cols=40 SIZE="90" ALIGN="left"></textarea></li>
</ul>
<p>Please type in the full address of all wrongdoers below:</p>
<ul>
<li><textarea name="doersaddress" rows=3 cols=40 SIZE="90" ALIGN="left"></textarea></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>What damages were suffered?</h4>
<p>Describe the damage suffered below:</p>
<ul>
<li><textarea name="damage" rows=3 cols=50 SIZE="250" ALIGN="left"></textarea></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>Has anyone already filed a suit?</h4>
<ul>
<li><input type=radio name="anyone" value="Yes">Yes <input type=radio name="anyone" value="No">No</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>What else should we know to help you?</h4>
<p>Type in any additional information we may need to assist you below:</p>
<ul>
<li><textarea name="helpyou" rows=3 cols=50 SIZE="250" ALIGN="left"></textarea></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>How Can We Help You?</h4>
<p>What is your goal? Explain here what you hope to achieve by working with a qualified lawyer on this issue.</p>
<ul>
<li><textarea name="goal" rows=3 cols=50 SIZE="250" ALIGN="left"></textarea></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>Are you interested in serving as a representative in a <a href="txt/complain.html#class">class action</a>?</h4>
<ul>
<li><input type=radio name="rep" value="Yes">Yes <input type=radio name="rep" value="No">No</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>When is the best time to reach you by telephone? (Indicate your time zone - e.g. PST, EST, etc.)</h4>
<ul>
<li><input type=text size=20 maxlength=256 name="time" ROWS="1" COLS="20"></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>If the information you have provided is complete, please press the <strong>Send</strong> button below to send it to The Alexander Law Firm. If you wish to start over, press the 
<strong>Clear all fields</strong> button below and re-enter all information. Your information will be kept confidential.</p>
