California State Bar Journal 314 (1979)</p>

<p><i>Videotape in the Courtroom</i>, 14 In Brief 50 (1978)</p>

<p><i>Privacy, Banking and the Supreme Court: A Before and After
Look at Miller</i>, 10 Southwestern University Law Review 13
(1978) with Robert Spurgeon</p>

<p><i>Arrest Record Expungement in California: The Polishing of
Sterling</i>, 9 University of San Francisco Law Review 299 (1974)
with Kathleen Walz, cited <i>Loder v. Municipal Court</i>, 17
C.3d 859, 868 (1976)</p>

<p><i>Grand Jury Indictment Versus Prosecution by Information -
An Equal Protection - Due Process Issue</i>, 25 Hastings Law
Journal 977 (1974) with Sheldon Portman, adopted, <i>Hawkins v.
Superior Court</i>, 22 C.3d 584 (1978), cited<i>Johnson v.
Superior Court</i>, 15 C.3d 248, 269 (1975) (Mosk, J.,
concurring)</p>

<p><i>The Right to Privacy and Arrest Record Retention of the
Innocent</i>, California Attorneys for Criminal Justice Forum,
May, 1974.</p>

<p><i>Consumers' Rights: A Primer for Delivering Legal Services</i>,
CAOC Tahoe Convention Handbook, April 1996</p>

