<hr>
<p>1996 Outstanding Achievement Award by Consumer Attorneys of California for exceptional service and contribution on 
behalf of injured victims and consumers, November, 1996.</p>
<p>Commendation for outstanding contributions to the delivery of pro bono legal services in Santa Clara County in 1995, by the 
Santa Clara County Bar Association and the Pro Bono Project of Santa Clara County, December, 1995. </p>
<p>Certified as a Civil Trial Advocate by the National Board of Trial Advocacy, 1980, recertified, 1985, 1990. The NBTA is the 
only board of trial specialists approved by the American Bar Association and the only national organization certifying civil trial 
lawyers based upon actual trial experience, evaluations by judges and opponents, peer review, and written examination. </p>
<p>Highest evaluation for legal ability [AV Rating] and ethical standards by nationally recognized Martindale-Hubbell </p>
<p>&quot;Recognized Trial Lawyer,&quot; California Trial Lawyers Association with experience in the fields of Products Liability, Insurance 
Bad Faith, General Personal Injury, and Professional Negligence litigation. First recognized in 1980 </p>
<p>National Bar Register of Preeminent Lawyers: Civil Trial, Personal Injury and Environmental Law </p>
<p>Founding Member, The National Association of Consumer Advocates, 1994 </p>
<p>First recipient of the &quot;Man of the Year&quot; Award by The Women's Fund 1980-93, a &quot;special recognition for supporting women 
and significantly contributing to the betterment of women in today's world.&quot; May, 1989 </p>
<p>Pro Bono Award for advocacy and service on behalf of persons injured in the work place by the Santa Clara Center for 
Occupational Safety and Health, August, 1993. First recipient of this award </p>
<p>Featured as a role model for community leadership efforts by author Tom Hayes, <i>You Can Make A Difference In Silicon 
Valley, </i>Far Western Graphics in Silicon Valley: 1994. </p>
<p>1990 Outstanding Achievement Award, California Trial Lawyers' Association </p>
<p>California Trial Lawyers Association President's Service Award, 1988 </p>
<p>Vice-President of The State Bar of California, 1987-88; Board of Governors, 1985-88 </p>
<p>Vice President of the California Trial Lawyers Association, 1995; Board of Governors 1990-94 </p>
<p>President, Santa Clara County Bar Association, 1984 </p>
<p>Fellow, Roscoe Pound-American Trial Lawyers Foundation </p>
<p>Mayor's Commendation for Distinguished Service, City of San Jose </p>
<p>Santa Clara County Youth Commission Medal </p>
<p>President, Democratic Century Club, 1992-94 </p>
<p>F.A.A. Licensed Pilot </p>
<p>Outstanding Young Man of America </p>
<p>Who's Who in the World</p>
<p>Who's Who in American Law</p>
<p>Who's Who in California</p>
<p>National Legal Commentator for &quot;Marketplace,&quot; a nationally broadcast business news program, heard on American Public 
Radio in 100 cities throughout the United States, 1989-1990. </p>
<p>Television moderator of &quot;Sound Off&quot;, 35 one hour public affairs programs focusing on current issues of public importance for 
KNTV - Channel 11, ABC Television, San Jose, Sundays, 6:00 p.m. for the 1981-1982 season. </p>
