<p>On this page:</p>
<p><a href="#personal"><img src="t-dn.gif" alt="**" align=middle width=20 height=35></a> <a href="#personal">Personal Information</a> || <a href="#refs"><img src="t-dn.gif" alt="**" align=middle width=20 height=35></a> <a href="#refs">References</a> || <a href="#additional"><img src="t-dn.gif" alt="**" align=middle width=20 height=35></a> <a href="#additional">Additional Information</a> </p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="personal">PERSONAL INFORMATION</a></h3>
<p>Born September 26, 1944, in Cleveland, Ohio. Married to Nancy Biebel of Toledo, Ohio, 1968. Children: Marshall, born, 
1972; Meredith, born, 1974. </p>
<p><strong>Office: </strong>55 S. Market Street, Suite 1080<br>
San Jose, California 95113<br>
(408) 289-1776; Fax 287-1776; TTY 286-177 </p>
<p>1300 Mercantile Library Building, 414 Walnut Street<br>
Cincinnati, OH 45202<br>
(513) 723-1776; Fax 421-1776</p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="refs">REFERENCES</a></h3>
<p>National Board of Trial Advocacy, Certification of Civil Trial Advocates, (617) 573-8700 </p>
<p>Consumer Attorneys of California, Statewide Recognized Experience Program, (800) 767-CTLA </p>
<p>Current president, or any past president, of the Santa Clara County Bar Association, (408) 287-2557 </p>
<p>Presiding Judge or any judge of the Santa Clara County Superior Court, (408) 299-2074 </p>
<p>Knowledge Index, Dialog, or Compuserve computer reports of the San Jose Mercury News </p>
<p>Martindale-Hubbell National Index of Attorneys, any county law library </p>
<p>Bar Register of Preeminent Lawyers, any county law library </p>
<hr>
<h3><a name="additional">ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</a></h3>
<p>In a class action, arising from the explosion of a tank car filled with sulfuric acid and sulfur trioxide in Richmond, California in 
1993 that injured 65,000 Californians, The Alexander Law Firm served as one of seven members of the Plaintiffs' Management 
Committee that controlled this litigation and negotiated a $180,000,000 settlement. Court documents contain the following peer 
evaluation: </p>
<blockquote>
<p>Richard Alexander of The Alexander Law Firm was designated as the Chairman of the Medical Causation 
Committee, which was created by the Class Action Executive Committee and remained active throughout the 
litigation. Mr. Alexander's experience in the field of toxic injury litigation was invaluable. (He) planned and 
executed the organization of plaintiffs' proof of scientific and medical evidence ... including the plume study and 
the screening of plaintiffs for the Model Complaint. Mr. Alexander actively participated in the planning, 
prosecution and settlement of the case.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Declaration of Liaison Counsel, Plaintiffs Management Committee In Support of Final Approval, In re GCC Richmond Works 
Case, Judicial Council Coordination Proceeding No. 2906, Contra Costa County Superior Court, Hearing October 27, 1995, 
Hon. Richard L. Patsey. Final Approval Decision November 13, 1995 confirmed the settlement as fair and reasonable. </p>
