<head>
<title>The National Consumer Complaint Center for Food, Drugs, Cosmetics, Medical Devices, Radiation-emitting Electronic Products, Veterinary Drugs and Feeds</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- looking find locate seeking search lawyer attorney litigation  law firm alexander richard , specializes handles does practices handles
consumer law tort class action(s) product liability defective products  toxic chemical(s)  fraud bodily injury personal injury pollution 
poison(s) environmental mass accident negligence aircrash, lives located resides practices california northern san jose nationally united states --><p><img src="cb-food.gif" alt=" " align=bottom width=120 height=144> </p>
<h3><a href="cb-intro.html">The National Consumer Complaint Center</a> for Food, Drugs, Cosmetics, Medical Devices, 
Radiation-emitting Electronic Products, Veterinary Drugs and Feeds</h3>
<hr>
<p>Before you report a product that you suspect caused an illness or injury, ask yourself the following: </p>
<ul>
<li>Did you use the product for other than its intended purpose? </li>
<li>Did you fail to follow carefully the instructions for the product? </li>
<li>Was the product old or outdated? </li>
<li>Do you have an allergy or other medical condition that might have something to do with the suspected harmful effect? </li>
</ul>
<p>If you answer &quot;yes&quot; to any of these questions, it's unlikely that reporting the problem will be of any benefit. (Nevertheless, you 
should, of course, get proper medical care for your injury, if necessary.) Otherwise, report any complaint concerning the 
following: </p>
<h3>Food</h3>
<p>Report any product, including seafood and dairy products (but not meat or poultry if it is unsafe, decomposed, filthy, or defective; 
contains foreign substances or particles, such as hair or insects; is not properly labeled; is processed or stored under insanitary 
conditions; weighs less than the labeled weight; or has caused injury or illness. </p>
<h3>Drugs</h3>
<p>Report products whose appearance is unusual--for example, a capsule that is cloudy or contains crystals when it should be clear; 
a package that has a part or parts of its tamper-evident safeguards missing or broken; a capsule or pill that is chipped, broken or 
off-color; or any product that is contaminated with foreign matter, such as hair or mold. Also, report any drug that has caused an 
injury or illness. </p>
<h3>Cosmetics</h3>
<p>Report products that contain filthy or harmful substances, are decomposed or spoiled, or have caused an injury. </p>
<h3>Medical Devices</h3>
<p>Report products that do not perform according to claims and instructions, have false or misleading labels, are labeled as sterile 
but have broken seals, or have caused an injury. </p>
<h3>Radiation-Emitting Electronic Products (such as microwave ovens or video display terminals)</h3>
<p>Report incidents in which an injury either has occurred or may occur from products that give off radiation. </p>
<h3>Veterinary Drugs and Feed</h3>
<p>Report the same problems with animal feed (including pet food) and veterinary drugs that would be reported for human foods or 
drugs. </p>
<hr>
<form action="http://seamless.com/cgi-bin/tsw-talf-cb-food.pl" method="POST">
<p><strong><input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="date"> = Date of incident</strong></p>
<p><strong>Description of the injuries or damage incurred =<br>
<textarea name="damage" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong><input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="type"> = Type of product involved</strong></p>
<p><strong>Brief description of the incident sequence =<br>
<textarea name="sequence" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong><input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="city"> = City and state where the incident occurred</strong></p>
<p><strong><input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="brand"> = Manufacturer, model, brand, name</strong></p>
<p><strong>Have you kept any opened or unopened containers or packages of the product (don't open packages if you haven't 
already done so) =<input type=radio name="kept" value="yes">Yes <input type=radio name="kept" value="no">No.</strong></p>
<p><strong><input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="codes"> = Describe any codes or identifying marks that appear on the label or container. 
(Usually these are stamped or embossed on the lids of canned products.)</strong></p>
<p><strong>Availability of the product for inspection and storage location =<br>
<textarea name="inspect" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Contact information for any state or local personnel who investigated the incident =<br>
<textarea name="contact" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Name and address of the doctor or hospital providing emergency medical treatment =<br>
<textarea name="doctor" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Name and address of the store where the product was purchased and the date of purchase =<br>
<textarea name="store" rows=5 cols=50></textarea> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Full name of one U.S. Senator from your state =</strong></p>
<p><strong>First Name <input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="senator1"><br>
Last Name <input type=text size=30 maxlength=90 name="senator2"> </strong></p>
<p><strong>Full name of your Congressional Representative =</strong></p>
<p><strong>First Name <input type=text size=20 maxlength=90 name="congress1"><br>
Last Name <input type=text size=30 maxlength=90 name="congress2"></strong></p>
<p><strong><input type=text size=30 maxlength=90 name="name"> Your name<br>
